 I've been thinking of joining the warrior fold as a nice change from clericing (lvl 26) and at the moment I'm tossing up between barbarian and dark elf.<br>
<br>
 The main reasons for these two is for the the barbarian can slam and the dark elf can SEE! There also seem to be far too many barbarians around, it'd be nice to look a little different from the masses.<br>
<br>
 Basically, I'm not bothered about stats really, I'd just like to know if giving up Slam is a large blow at the higher levels where letting a mob getting a spell off can really hurt. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Also, how screwed are dark elves for trusty old faction in Kunark, will I be able to enter FV if I kill enough sarnaks?<br>
<br>
 Aramir, soon to be dishing it out instead of healing it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Guunthar Dgunn</span><br> <b>is too scared to Register</b><br>   <font color=#FF0000>(10/17/00 9:55:17 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Slam or Sight</span><hr size=1> Ok, if you care about weather or not missing out on slam will hurt you in the later levels, and dont care about stats, you need to reprioratize your warrior. <br>
<br>
I personaly would not play a barbarian becuase 1) everyone plays them. 2) Horrible Eye sight. 3) Too low of str in my oppinion. 4) they are just not my taste. <br>
<br>
I play an ogre, I get infravision, which is nice, however you still need a GL stone. We get the highest primary stats. I dont like to worry about my size because I am thinking about the long term. and in the losg term, I am going to have a cobalt bracer (effect shrink). and I get slam, and good stats. I dont care much for regen because I will always be grouped at that level, and besides, with so many hp, regen does not do a whole lot. That and its almost impossible to solo anything worth good exp. <br>
<br>
Another reason that you have to play for is the look you want. If you cant stand looking at yourself, then dont play ogre. If you dont care, like me, and take yourself as a badass, then congrats. Hlaf elves look great, and that is why a lot of people play them. <br>
<br>
But back to your sight vs. Slam, slam will be much much more of a blessing to you. And the Cobalt helm is effect infra. so dont give to much of a care. <br>
<br>
In my oppinion slam is more potent then a non combat related abbility, for the whole reason of our exhistance is to take and dish out damage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubaarakorchammer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BaarakOrchammer</A></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/17/00 10:10:39 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Slam or Sight</span><hr size=1> Baahh don't listen the ogre! The Barbarians are the ultimate warrior!<br>
<br>
Actually he has a lot of good points about size and regen etc. A lot of tests done <br>
lately show that strength does not really make a big difference in the greater sheme <br>
of damage output. A ogre with 200+ str is not putting out that much more damage<br>
than a gnome with 110 str. It sucks but there it is..Now high stamina at the upper levels<br>
is a different story <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I prefer the large races for slam. Ogres cannot be stunned from the front. Very cool.<br>
Trolls regen, nice thing to have but you will be grouped with a healer. Both have terrible<br>
faction. Barbarian stats are good, they get slam, and their faction is decent. And<br>
they have horned helms! They have no night vision, but you get used to it, and there<br>
are items that bestow infravision.<br>
<br>
All races make good warriors. Play what you want. Slam is a really nice bonus though. <br>
<br>
<br>
Baarak Orchammer<br>
Wolf of the North <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uvargyr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vargyr</A></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/17/00 10:13:13 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Slam or Sight</span><hr size=1> if your looking for originality, ya cant go wrong with dark elf! I am often asked to fear mobs cause no one can comprehend a de warrior! LOL yep, thats me the sk in full crafted =Op As far as slam goes, I really wish I had it, in fact I've started training up my bash skill lately to help in duels with wigglers and fightng caster mobs. I think that the large race warriors are superior stat wise, but if your a old school RP'r like me make a de if you like a challenge, or half elf if you like the pretty woosy look. Honestly though, i hold my own in a fight and have never lost to a large race in a duel (cause i run around and its hard to target me and keep me in front). I think playing a ogre or troll could be fun though, may make one once vargyr hits 50th or so. <p>Vargyr Kaine 30ish warrior of brell <br>
Fauls 16...15...16 druid of Tribunal <br>
Deadcalm 17th necro of Brell <br>
Blasti constantly remade gnome of Test <br>
"If ya aint dyin, ya aint tryin!"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uchutbashu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chut Bashu</A></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/17/00 10:20:07 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bash or Sight?</span><hr size=1> Me iz Chut Ogre Warrior on Tallon Zek, Race War.<br>
<br>
Me thought fer musta ben dayz on to be born, Ogre, Iksar, Dark Elf, or Trollie.<br>
<br>
Me decide on Ogre.  Me made right call, EXCEPT me do all over again me max out Stamina first den dex and Str.<br>
<br>
Okies here iz da dinking.... OOC... I assume not on Race war so I leave those reasons out of the discussion<br>
<br>
Iksar<br>
Pro: Best begining area, New Armors, Kunark, Regen<br>
Con: Bad Faction (hard to bind), EXP penalty huge<br>
<br>
Dark Elf<br>
Pro: Vision, Looks great in Fine Steal Plate<br>
Con: Too weak.  Damage is not the issue, Hit Points and carrying capacity is a huge handicap.<br>
<br>
Troll<br>
Pro: Regen, Slam<br>
Con: EXP penalty, large Size<br>
<br>
Ogre<br>
Pro: Slam, Better Stats than Troll<br>
Con: Large Size<br>
<br>
In the end, I decided on an Ogre.<br>
<br>
Now if you choose Dark Elf, I think you can have as much fun as I am having with your character.  It is all about how you define your fun.<br>
<br>
For me, fun is being able to Roleplay a Ogre while not having to worry about my weight (after playing an Iksar monk to 45 trust me this is annoying).<br>
<br>
If I wanted to be a Dark Elf, more than I wanted to be a warrior, I would be a Dark Elf Rogue.<br>
<br>
BTW it is not Bash or sight.... but SLAM or sight.  Bash means you are using a shield.  No warrior should be using a shield after he gets dual wield.  Either two weapons or one 2 hander.<br>
<br>
Just my thoughts <p>CHUT<BR>
Ogre<BR>
Master Potter<BR>
Master Brewer<BR>
Master Fletcher<BR>
Strugggling Tailor<BR>
Frustrated Fisher "stop askn wut me doin u scare da fishies"<BR>
