</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uchutbashu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chut Bashu</A> at: 10/17/00 10:21:43 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Guunthar Dgunn</span><br> <b>is too scared to Register</b><br>   <font color=#FF0000>(10/17/00 1:50:52 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   bash or sight</span><hr size=1> When you slam, you are in effect bashing them. and ths skill is called bash.Or at least its what goes up<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uathasicebeast.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Athas Icebeast</A></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 173<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/17/00 4:52:41 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.users.uswest.net/~jlorfing/members/athas.jpg WIDTH=48 HEIGHT=211></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: bash or sight</span><hr size=1> i play a barbarian.  barbarians can build str just as high as ogres, so that is not an issue.  back when i was in early 40s, i had more str then any ogre (211 unbuff).  it is not str that makes the warrior.  it is the armor class and hitpoints, so if you make a barbarian warrior, put all points into stamina.  when you hit planes, you will be happy.<br>
<br>
as for slam, imho it is so much better then kick that it's worth playing a large race.  i have saved my groups numerous times by interrupting a caster npc from healing themselves.  <br>
<br>
as for the vision, i never let it get to me.  in dungeons it's not a big deal, since a lightstone will make any dungeon bright as the sun.  in outside zones it can be tricky.  whenever i am traveling, or pulling monsters in the nightime, i put on my infravision ring.  it runs for about 200-500pp, and it isn't hard to get for a full group of 25s.  you wont really need it before then.  <br>
<br>
anyhow, i agree with most of the points above, i jusst thought i should post my own &quot;pros&quot; of playing a barbarian.  be whatever suits you the most.<br>
